To start we need to calculate all the data related to the loan. 

## First step: Calculate the annual payment of the loan

To determine the annual loan payment, we can use the formula from previous sections where the present value of the annuity is the result of multiplying the annual payment times the annuity factor. 

$$
\begin{equation}
\text{Present value of annuity} = \text{Annual payment}\times \frac{1-\frac{1}{(1+r)^t}}{r}  
\end{equation}
$$             

If we clear the formula, we can determine the annuity as follows: 
$$
\begin{equation}
\text{Annual payment} =\frac{\text{Present value of annuity}}{\dfrac{1-\frac{1}{(1+r)^t}}{r}}  
\end{equation}
$$ 

Then, 
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Annual payment} &=\frac{\$4,800,000}{\dfrac{1-\frac{1}{(1+0.08)^4}}{0.08}} \\[30pt] 
&= \frac{\$4,800,000}{3.31212684}\\[10pt] 
&= \$1,449,219.86 
\end{align*}
$$

***The annual payment for the loan is $\bold{\$1,449,219.86}$***.
